title: For Sale:  No guns allowed at the GSR show
postcontent: BEWARE OF THE GSR SHOW THIS WEEKEND 10, 11 AND 12, 2017. The Big Reno Show at the GSR will not allow you to bring any gun on to their property. They are turning you around at the door if you do. CCW Also, no CCW is allowed. Yes, you read this correctly, the GSR will not allow you to bring any firearms of any type on their property. The have signs posted as you enter the casino. They have security guards posted at the doors checking your bags as you enter, also they are wanding everyone who enters the show. You cannot bring anything to sell, trade or repair. The vendors are all pissed, some didnt even show. There are empty tables, when there shouldn't be. If you buy more the one gun, they make you leave out the back of building. You cannot have both ammo and a gun at the same time. They make you take it to your vehicle in two trips. If you buy more than 50 rounds they will escort you to you car so you can drop it off before you will be allowed to re-enter, if you buy more than 1000 rounds, they make you go to the loading dock to pick it up. You can't take a gun out through the casino like years past. They are searching bags as you leave also. There are police everywhere. They are nice, but a show of force. Vendors that are selling at the show can't have any guns in their rooms. Be careful here. There are some nice vendors getting screwed by the GSR. There are still some deals to be had, but because of the idoit in Vegas, they are in stupid mode.

title: For Sale:  Remington 700 AAC-SD, 300 BLK, HS Precision Stock + More
postcontent: I have a Remington 700 AAC-SD Tactical 300 BLK  in good condition.  This was a straight impulse buy.  Thought I may use it as a coyote gun, but all it has done is sit in the safe.  Following is a list of modifications that have been installed/done to the rifle:-HS Precision aluminum bedded stock.  The stock was originally purchased with my Rem 700 5R Gen 2.  I purchased a new stock for the 5R and installed the HS on the 300 BLK.  The original Houge stock has been trashed.-LaRue Remington 700 Short Action Rail (Model LT1135)-Surefire Socom Muzzle Break (5/8x24), I still have the OEM thread protector-Harris S-BRM Bipod 6"-9", Leg Notch, Sling Swivel Stud Mount-Vortex Viper PST 30 mm Low Rings**There is one issue with the firearm besides the amateur paint job.  When installing the LaRue rail I experienced a hardware failure pertaining to the front screw.  When tightening, the top of the screw snapped, leaving what was threaded in the mounting hole.  LaRue recommends tightening to 15 inch-pounds the screw failed at 10.  I filled the remaining hole with hardening compound.  I haven't experienced any instability or shift.  When painting the rifle the action and trigger were properly taped off.  All internals are clean and functioning**Asking price was determined by taking current online pricing (Bud's, Cheaper Than Dirt, etc.) and discounting the total price by 30%.  I also deducted $175 for the issue with the rail and my custom paint job.Buyer must present valid ID (CCW preferred) and be willing to sign a bill of sale and meet in a public location.  I usually like to conduct business outside the Spring Hill PD.  ** PRICE IS FIRM, NO TRADE OFFERS WILL BE CONSIDERED**

title: For Sale:  Ruger SR556e AR15 rifle
postcontent:
This is one of the 'nice' Ruger AR's. It operates with a piston system rather than DI which allows the gun to stay cooler and cleaner during operation, meaning less fouling of the bolt. You can also dial an adjustment to the piston to account for different types of ammunition. The gun is very reliable.  This is a fine AR rifle, one that looks new with few rounds shot. 
Rifle features a 16 1/2" cold hammer forged mil-spec 41v45 barrel. Barrel is threaded 1/2-28 and capped with a Ruger flash suppressor. Lightweight ergonomic handguard, flattop receiver with full length picatinny rail in the 12 o'clock position. 6-position telescopic stock on a mil-spec buffer tube. Chrome lined gas block and chrome plated piston. Includes (1) 30-round PMAG's and a Ruger soft-side carrying case.  I also swapped out the OEM grip with a Magpul grip and IMI Defense Automatic Deploy Weaver Picatinny Flip up Sights. Would consider trades for a nice deer rifle (scope) of equal value.

It features a 4.41” barrel, an overall length of 8.2”, and an ambidextrous manual safety. PLUS, 1000 rounds RARE FN ammo = 550 rounds SS195LF HOT ammo (11 Boxes of 50 rounds per/box) and 450 rounds RARE SS192 "Green Ammo" (9 Boxes of 50 rounds per/box). RARE SS192 “Green Ammo” was produced for ONLY 3 months before FN turned to the SS195LF. The SS192 "Green Ammo" is the predecessor to the current SS195LF which uses the same 27gr HP aluminum core bullet but with a lead free primer, hence the LF designation. The SS192 “green ammo” or environmentally friendly ammo was SS195LF ammo before they changed the name and box. The manufacture (FN Herstal) relates the labeling as a way to visibly mark the packaging so that there is a lower chance for this to be mixed up with SS192 ammunition that contains lead primer.

title: For Sale:  Springfield 1911 Range Officer 9mm 5" bbl PI9129L
postcontent:
New In Box, never fired; selling off some of my collection. Private party sale to NV residents. More info: 
Springfield 1911 Range Officer 9mm 5" bbl Specifications: Caliber: 9mm Barrel: 5" Stainless Steel Match Grade, Fully Supported Ramp Sights: Fiber Optic Front With Low Profile Combat Rear Magazines: 2 - 9+1 Round, Blued Grips: Cross Cannon Double Diamond Cocobolo Weight w/Empty Magazine: 41 oz Frame: Forged Carbon Steel; Parkerized Slide: Forged Carbon Steel, Parkerized Recoil System: GI Style Length: 8.6" MFG P/N: PI9129L  
New In Box. Private party sale to NV residents. 
For shooters who need a competition 1911, the Range Officer from Springfield Armory offers finely tuned performance without breaking the bank. It brings the precision of a competition pistol in a simple and straightforward configuration. The Range Officer has the same quality forged national match frame and slide as the Trophy Match and TRP 1911s, with the same precision fit. Add in the same national match stainless steel barrel and bushing, and you have a pistol that shoots well beyond its price tag. This competition-grade pistol features a 5" stainless steel, match-grade barrel and a GI style recoil system. The beavertail grip safety, extended lightweight trigger and flat mainspring housing allow the pistol to sit in your hand comfortably for long periods of time at the range. It has a Parkerized forged carbon steel frame and slide. It is finished with double diamond cocobolo grips and includes two 9-round blued steel magazines. It all adds up to a pistol that will let you seriously compete in a variety of matches.
